    "These exhibit many interesting physical phenomena involving localized symmetries (which are possibly non-invertible), induced 1-form symmetries, and interactions between localized and induced symmetries.",
    "Ultimately, we argue that all these physical phenomena are neatly encapsulated as information describing a 3-representation of the 2-group associated to the 1-form symmetry group.",
